<br>
If someone could tell me exactly where this huge &quot;melee advantage&quot; is, i would really appreciate it because it would help my day to day play. <br>
<br>
Lets set up this scenario. My Troll self is banking in Neriak. Gosh, it sure is hard to move around in there... all the little inkies blocking my way. Suddenly I'm hit by Ice Comet. There goes a quarter of my life. Roughly 15 seconds later I'm dead. I never saw where he was casting from. I had NO chance to fight back in the least, and I couldn't even get out of the bank for the little Tier'Dal asking me if i could spare some money for their level 4 spells. This happens constantly on RZ. Not just to warriors. All it takes for a wizard to drop someone cold is for them to have a target and a predisposed victim. Thats all there is to it. It takes about 4 ICs to drop me. How many would it take to drop your wiz? Especially if say, you already have something targeted. If you even hope to fight back you have to take the first IC, empty your target, take the second IC, hope it doesnt kill you, track down the offending wizard in his hiding place and somehow do the damage that he has done to you in that time. Remove the damage cap? you wouldnt even have a chance to get a target. Thats the simple truth. <br>
<br>
Lets not mention that all it takes to cancel out my melee is a diamond skin and levi. And casters are at a disadvantage? <br>
<br>
Make every spell in PvP line of sight, then we'll talk about the logic of removing the cap. <br>
<br>
Log onto RZ one night. Ask around and get the names of a few PvP guilds. Talk to an officer, ask how many tanks they have over level 50 in their guild, and listen to them laugh at you. Yeah, as a warrior i have enough HP to get my dropables bagged, but there really isnt any fight. <br>
<br>
In a face to face duel, it would be a good fight. Ive beaten wizards in friendly duels. Ive also been beaten. Its pretty even in that aspect. <br>
<br>
You complain around enough and get the &quot;outdated&quot; damage cap removed, and you've ruined 3 servers (Sullon doesnt count).<br>
<br>
I love PvP. Thats why im on Rallos... the most PvP of PvP. Ive rambled a bit, and i dont mean to seem so argumentative. Its just that ive played on this server since a few weeks after it went live. I know how PvP works, and ive played almost every class. Casters, especially wizards, have an advantage. Is it an unfair advantage? No. But in my opinion its completely incorrect to say that you're at some crippling disadvantage that needs to be addressed.<br>
<br>
I would be more than happy to answer any questions that some of you may be curious about. My mind is made on the subject, but that doesnt mean it cant be changed. Do you have any suggestions on how things could be done to make melee and caster alike happy? <br>
